Misir Wot

1/2 c evoo
3 finely chopped medium red onions (2c)
10 minced garlic cloves
3" fresh ginger, peeled and minced
3 tbsp berbere + more for sprinkling
2 tsp finely ground nigella seeds (aka black caraway, roman coriander, nutmeg flower, fennel flower)
1 tsp ground cardamom
kosher salt
freshly ground pepper
3 c red lentils (1 1/4 lbs)


In a large enameled cast-iron casserole, heat the olive oil. Add the onions and cook over moderate heat until the are softened and just starting to brown, ~8min. Add the garlic, ginger, berbere, nigella seeds, cardamon, and a generous pinch of salt and pepper and cook until fragrant and deeply colored, ~10m.
Add the red lentils with 8c water to the casserole and bring to a boil. Cover and cook over moderately low heat, stirring occasionally, until the lentils have cooked down and thickened, ~25m. Season the lentils with salt and pepper. Sprinkle with berbere when serving.
